 Speaker of Abia State House of Assembly, Chinedum Orji, has secured the Peoples Democratic Party Ticket for Ikwuano/Umuahia Federal Constituency by defeating five other aspirants. Announcing the result of the primary which ended at about 5:43pm at the Kanu Nwankwo Indoor Sports Hall of the Umuahia Township Stadium, the State Returning Officer for the Federal House of Representatives Ticket for the party, Chief Mezie Nwau­bani said 90 delegates partici­pated in the delegates primary. -Advertisement- According to the party’s returning officer, Chief Chinedum Orji scored 86 votes, while his closes rival, Chief Obi Aguocha managed to score eight votes and the third placed went to a for­mer Umuahia North Council Chairman, Chief Chidiebere Nwachukwu who scored two votes.